28/01/2010
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- Support for NATO accession is rising, according to the latest survey by the Ipsos Strategic Marketing agency, published Wednesday (January 27th). The December poll of more than 800 people suggests that 40% of Montenegrins support membership in the Alliance if there was a referendum while 44% would oppose it. Previous polls had put the level of support at around 30%. (RTCG, Cafemontenegro, Makfax - 27/01/10)
